cs.MM, cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CV, cs.HC 

The paper deals with video streaming and Quality of Experience (QoE), which suggests that it could belong to multiple sub-categories. 

- cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with video streaming and QoE, which falls under the domain of multimedia. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper proposes a rate-adaptation algorithm and admission control policy to optimize network resource consumption, which suggests that it could belong to the networking and internet architecture sub-category. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with optimizing video transmission with QoE constraints, which could fall under the domain of information theory. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper deals with video quality fluctuations, which could fall under the domain of computer vision and pattern recognition. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper deals with QoE, which is related to human perception and interaction with technology, suggesting that it could belong to the human-computer interaction sub-category.
